@startuml

title Safehome Security Function State Transition Diagram

initial : Power-on;
state "Power-on" as P {
    initial
}
state "Startup Problem" as S1
state "Ready to Use" as R
state "Monitoring" as M
state "Alarm Activated" as A
state "False Alarm/Time Ends" as F
state "Off" as O

P --> S1 : Check if everything is working upon power-on
S1 --> P : Stop if there is a problem during startup
P --> R : Become ready to use if everything is fine during startup
R --> M : Allow user to activate it when it is ready to use
R --> A : Allow user to reset it when it is ready to use
R --> O : Allow user to turn it off when it is ready to use
M --> A : Start monitoring if it is activated
A --> F : Start the alarm and send alerts if a sensor is triggered during monitoring
F --> M : Continue monitoring if it turns out to be a false alarm or the time ends
R --> P : Stop and return to normal when the user enters the password at any time

@enduml
